---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

const schema = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Interactive Travel Credit Card Comparison Tool",
    "description": "Input your monthly spending to find the best travel credit card for your specific lifestyle and travel goals.",
    "author": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "Migrating Mammals"
    }
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How does this comparison tool work?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "By inputting your estimated monthly spend in categories like dining, travel, and groceries, the tool calculates the estimated annual rewards value for top cards."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Does the tool account for annual fees?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes, to find the true net value of a card, you must subtract the annual fee from the estimated rewards earned. Our methodology accounts for this."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Should I choose a card based solely on spending?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "No. While earning rates are important, you should also factor in benefits like lounge access, no foreign transaction fees, and travel insurance."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
];

export const meta = {
  title: "Interactive Travel Card Comparison Tool",
  description: "Input your monthly spending to find the best travel credit card for your specific lifestyle and travel goals.",
  category: "tool",
  published: "2026-03-15",
};
---

<SiteLayout site="migratingmammals" title="Interactive Travel Card Comparison Tool" description="Input your monthly spending to find the best travel credit card for your specific lifestyle and travel goals." canonical="https://migratingmammals.com/travel-card-comparison-tool" schema={schema}>
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>Travel Card Comparison Tool</h1>
      <p>Input spending, see the best card for you.</p>
    </div>

    <section>
      <h2>Find Your Perfect Match</h2>
      <p>Choosing the right travel credit card from our <a href="/travel-credit-cards-compared">comprehensive list</a> can be overwhelming. The "best" card isn't the same for everyone; it depends entirely on where you spend your money and how you value perks like <a href="/lounge-access-cards">lounge access</a> and <a href="/no-fx-fee-cards">no foreign transaction fees</a>.</p>
      <p>Use the calculator below to estimate your annual rewards based on your spending habits.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div class="card" id="calculator">
        <h3>Estimated Monthly Spend</h3>
        <div style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">
          <label style="display:block; margin-bottom:0.5rem; color:var(--text-secondary);">Dining & Restaurants ($):</label>
          <input type="number" id="spendDining" value="500" style="width:100%; padding:0.5rem; border-radius:4px; border:1px solid var(--border-color); background:var(--bg-color); color:var(--text-primary);" />
        </div>
        <div style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">
          <label style="display:block; margin-bottom:0.5rem; color:var(--text-secondary);">Travel & Transit ($):</label>
          <input type="number" id="spendTravel" value="400" style="width:100%; padding:0.5rem; border-radius:4px; border:1px solid var(--border-color); background:var(--bg-color); color:var(--text-primary);" />
        </div>
        <div style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">
          <label style="display:block; margin-bottom:0.5rem; color:var(--text-secondary);">Groceries ($):</label>
          <input type="number" id="spendGroceries" value="300" style="width:100%; padding:0.5rem; border-radius:4px; border:1px solid var(--border-color); background:var(--bg-color); color:var(--text-primary);" />
        </div>
        <div style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
          <label style="display:block; margin-bottom:0.5rem; color:var(--text-secondary);">All Other Spend ($):</label>
          <input type="number" id="spendOther" value="1000" style="width:100%; padding:0.5rem; border-radius:4px; border:1px solid var(--border-color); background:var(--bg-color); color:var(--text-primary);" />
        </div>
        <button id="calcBtn" style="width:100%; padding:0.75rem; background:var(--accent-color); color:#fff; border:none; border-radius:4px; font-weight:bold; cursor:pointer;">Calculate Best Card</button>

        <div id="results" style="margin-top: 2rem; display:none;">
          <h3>Estimated Annual Rewards (Net of Fees)</h3>
          <ul id="resultsList" style="list-style-type:none; padding:0;"></ul>
          <p style="font-size:0.85rem; color:var(--text-secondary); margin-top:1rem;">*Estimates assume a base value of 1.5 cents per point for premium cards. Does not include sign-up bonuses.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Beyond the Math: Qualitative Factors</h2>
      <p>While the calculator provides a mathematical baseline, it doesn't account for qualitative benefits that might be dealbreakers for you.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Insurance:</strong> Does the card offer primary rental car coverage? Check our guide on <a href="/travel-insurance-credit-cards">travel insurance</a>.</li>
        <li><strong>Redemption Style:</strong> Do you prefer the simplicity of statement credits or transferring to airline partners? Read our <a href="/points-vs-cashback-travel">points vs. cashback analysis</a>.</li>
        <li><strong>Location:</strong> Ensure you are looking at cards available in your region. We have specific guides for the <a href="/best-travel-card-us">best US cards</a> and the <a href="/best-travel-card-canada">best Canadian cards</a>.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>If you're an advanced user looking to maximize returns beyond standard spending, consider learning about <a href="/guide-credit-card-churning">credit card churning strategies</a>.</p>
    </section>
  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
      const calcBtn = document.getElementById('calcBtn');
      if (calcBtn) {
        calcBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
          const dining = parseFloat(document.getElementById('spendDining').value) || 0;
          const travel = parseFloat(document.getElementById('spendTravel').value) || 0;
          const groceries = parseFloat(document.getElementById('spendGroceries').value) || 0;
          const other = parseFloat(document.getElementById('spendOther').value) || 0;

          // Simplified mock calculation logic for demonstration
          const cards = [
            { name: "Premium Travel Card A", fee: 95, diningM: 3, travelM: 2, grocM: 1, otherM: 1, cpp: 0.015 },
            { name: "Luxury Travel Card B", fee: 395, diningM: 1, travelM: 3, grocM: 1, otherM: 2, cpp: 0.015 },
            { name: "Dining/Grocery Card C", fee: 250, diningM: 4, travelM: 1, grocM: 4, otherM: 1, cpp: 0.015 },
            { name: "Flat Cashback Card D", fee: 0, diningM: 2, travelM: 2, grocM: 2, otherM: 2, cpp: 0.01 }
          ];

          const results = cards.map(card => {
            const monthlyPoints = (dining * card.diningM) + (travel * card.travelM) + (groceries * card.grocM) + (other * card.otherM);
            const annualPoints = monthlyPoints * 12;
            const grossValue = annualPoints * card.cpp;
            const netValue = grossValue - card.fee;
            return { name: card.name, netValue: netValue };
          });

          results.sort((a, b) => b.netValue - a.netValue);

          const resultsList = document.getElementById('resultsList');
          resultsList.innerHTML = '';
          results.forEach((res, index) => {
            const li = document.createElement('li');
            li.style.padding = '0.5rem 0';
            li.style.borderBottom = '1px solid var(--border-color)';
            li.innerHTML = `<strong>#${index + 1} ${res.name}:</strong> $${res.netValue.toFixed(2)} / year`;
            resultsList.appendChild(li);
          });

          document.getElementById('results').style.display = 'block';
        });
      }
    });
  </script>

  <style is:inline>
    .page-content { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.5rem; }
    .hero { text-align: center; padding: 3rem 0 2rem; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .hero p { color: var(--text-secondary); }
    .card { background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; margin: 1.5rem 0; }
    h2 { font-size: 1.8rem; margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--text-primary); }
    h3 { font-size: 1.4rem; margin-top: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; color: var(--text-primary); }
    p { margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text-secondary); }
    ul, ol { margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-left: 2rem; color: var(--text-secondary); }
    li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; line-height: 1.6; }
    a { color: var(--accent-color); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; }
    a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  </style>
</SiteLayout>
